  "local_port": 44148,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I A2A a Quora user?",
  "response": "\"A2A\" stands for \"Asked to Answer\" on Quora. When you \"A2A\" a Quora user, you are inviting them to contribute their answer to a specific question. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. **Find the Question**: Navigate to the question you want to ask someone to answer.\n\n2. **Click on the \"...\" Menu**: Located below the question title, there\u2019s a \"...\" (more options) button. Click on it.\n\n3. Select **\"Ask to Answer\"**: From the dropdown menu, select the \"Ask to Answer\" option.\n\n4. **Search for the User**: A search box will appear where you can type the name of the Quora user you want to invite. Select their username from the dropdown suggestions.\n\n5. **Send the Invitation**: Once you\u2019ve selected the user, click the \"Send\" button. The user will receive a notification inviting them to answer the question.\n\nAdditionally, you can \"A2A\" someone directly from their profile:\n\n1. **Go to Their Profile**: Visit the profile of the Quora user you want to invite.\n\n2. **Click the \"...\" Menu**: On their profile, click the \"...\" (more options) button.\n\n3. Select **\"Ask to Answer\"**: Choose this option from the dropdown menu.\n\n4. **Search for the Question**: A search box will appear where you can type in the question you want them to answer. Select the question from the dropdown suggestions and send the invitation.\n\nThe user will receive a notification and can choose to respond if they wish. Note that not all users may respond to A2A requests, and some may have their notifications set to limit such requests.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
